                                "text": "because it benefited us. Stallman’s crusade was off to the side of things like BSD, &c., and many of us believed at the time that less encumbered software was simply more free (“here it is, do what you want with it”). We did not at the time foresee a future when large corporations would run on our code without giving support to the people writing and maintaining it. In some sense we succeeded beyond our expectations and are now being punished for it."
